Narrator

The city sustained heavy damage when Rizia reconquered it in the 1920s. Attempts had been made to revitalize it, but several bombed-out, derelict buildings still stood in its center.

Narrator

In the dimming light of the setting sun, I could just make out an old mural painted on its side -- an angular, 1920s-style depiction of a paleacci, defaced almost beyond recognition.

Narrator

Immediately, the atmosphere transformed. We were in a chic-looking lounge, its furnishings sleek and understated. The soft strains of jazz filled the air.

Player_Romus

"Isn't this public? What if someone talks?"

Narrator

She smiled conspiratorially.

Player_Romus

"Ironjaw?"

Lucita Azaro

"I don't know how you deal with it. My own guards are paid very handsomely to leave me alone."

Player_Romus

"I'll try the Terador Tea."

Player_Romus

"Just sparkling water for me."

Narrator

Lucita nodded approvingly.

Lucita Azaro

"There it is. The country that gave us so much grief."

Lucita Azaro

"There it is. Our new business partner."

Player_Romus

"You sound skeptical."

Player_Romus

"I can't believe our fathers wanted us to invade. Our current arrangement makes so much more sense."

Player_Romus

"Maybe it won't take a war for Pales to reunite with Rizia. We can find an economic solution."

Lucita Azaro

"You know who doesn't? My father."

Lucita Azaro

"So will General Taddeus Azaro."

Player_Romus

"I can't believe we came so close to war. It would've been a terrible mistake."

Lucita Azaro

"Given our lack of investment in the military, our showing would've been quite poor. Better to play it safe than risk losing even more of the country."

Player_Romus

"I wish I'd had the nerve to order an invasion. All that hassle and we didn't even get a share of the gas field."

Player_Romus

"Are you disappointed we didn't start a war?"

Lucita Azaro

"As long as Pales holds up its end of the bargain."

Lucita Azaro

"As long as Lespia is in the picture, it won't be easy."

Lucita Azaro

"And even if the Palesians can be trusted, can Lespia?"

Player_Romus

"Not by choice. But it was either this, or start a war."

Player_Romus

"That's amazing news."

Player_Romus

"What a shame. I was looking forward to watching you order our troops around."

Player_Romus

"Bullshit, Lucita. I know you were behind the Pales border attack."

Narrator

Shock and rage exploded on her face.

Narrator

Just then, the server returned with our drinks.

Narrator

He carefully placed my water and Lucita's beer on the table.

Narrator

Lucita waited until he was gone to speak.

Player_Romus

"You're too beautiful to rot in prison."

Player_Romus

"I want to go to war with you by my side."

Player_Romus

"Because now I have you and your family completely at my mercy. If I want something from you, you're going to give it to me."

Player_Romus

"War with Pales was always going to be inevitable. If you didn't start something, I would have."

Player_Romus

"I'm still unsure whether you planned the attack. I wanted to see how you'd react when I accused you."

Lucita Azaro

"It is, isn't it?"

Player_Romus

"I trust our troops will obey him this time around."

Player_Romus

"We don't need his help. Look at how strong our military is now."

Player_Romus

"Come on. There must be some part of you that's excited by the idea of crushing the Palesians to a pulp."

Player_Romus

"Who are these people?"

Player_Romus

"Will he be fit enough to resume his old position?"

Player_Romus

"Are you sure about that? Because the border investigation results seemed to imply otherwise."

Lucita Azaro

"Your Majesty, I..."

Player_Romus

"To House Azaro."

Narrator

She looked me in the eye as our glasses clinked.

Narrator

She looked me in the eye as our glasses clinked.

Narrator

She looked me in the eye as our glasses clinked.

Narrator

She looked me in the eye as our glasses clinked.

Narrator

She looked at me as if I'd grown a second head.

Lucita Azaro

"He's been out of commission for too long."

Lucita Azaro

"I wanted to tell you something while we were here."

Player_Romus

"Tell them to take it up with my complaint department. It's in Caleqebiz Prison."

Player_Romus

"The Azaros are turning against me? That's not good."

Lucita Azaro

"We'll have a hell of a hard time winning the war if we can't marshall support from my family."

Lucita Azaro

"This is rather serious, I'm afraid."

Lucita Azaro

"We could've taken the whole field without a struggle. If we'd invested more in the military, I mean."

Narrator

She paused in contemplation.

Player_Romus

"A strong military is like a theater costume. You want to have it for the show, but it's ridiculous to use it in real life."

Player_Romus

"As long as Lespia's lurking about, we would have lost again."

Player_Romus

"I took the throne with the aim of avoiding conflict. I am proud to have stayed the course."

Player_Romus

"I'm a lover, not a fighter."

Narrator

She gave my a sly smile.

Player_Romus

"And how is House Azaro feeling about the fact that we aren't at war right now?"

Lucita Azaro

"Actually, Your Majesty, they--"

Narrator

Her brow furrowed.

Lucita Azaro

"Given our lack of investment in the military, our showing would've been quite poor. Better to play it safe than risk losing even more of the country."

Lucita Azaro

"I don't only mean him."

Lucita Azaro

"I hate to say it, but too many unpopular decisions *will* affect you."

Lucita Azaro

"They are not asking for special privileges. Only for acknowledgement."

Lucita Azaro

"You understand, then."

Lucita Azaro

"I've heard rumors of your plans to change the Rizian government. They won't make it off the ground without my family's support."

Lucita Azaro

"How romantic of you."

Narrator

A look of confusion spread across her face.

Lucita Azaro

"I have tried to justify your actions to the others. But there's only so much I can explain away."

Lucita Azaro

"I shouldn't be troubling you with all this on the eve of a war."

Lucita Azaro

"Simply put, Your Majesty, my family likes order."

Lucita Azaro

"So there are some who see your rather relaxed attitude towards our kingdom's national security as a direct affront."

Lucita Azaro

"And they are worried that the public's declining opinion of you may result in instability on a mass scale."

Lucita Azaro

"While we're here, I wanted to thank you for everything you've done for House Azaro over the past years."

Lucita Azaro

"That's very sweet. I congratulate you on managing both."

Lucita Azaro

"You've managed one of those. The second will surely follow."

Lucita Azaro

"So far, they do."

Narrator

I felt her foot brush against mine under the table.

Lucita Azaro

"I confess there are a few holdouts who wish the Pales gas dispute had ended with an annexation."

Lucita Azaro

"I personally wish you had made a larger commitment to Rizia's national defense than your predecessor. But there's still time."

Lucita Azaro

"Your readiness to defend Rizia against Palesian aggression won you many admirers in Cardesse-Montaklar."

Lucita Azaro

"But your commitment to maintaining our internal security even in the midst of an international crisis is very reassuring."

Lucita Azaro

"Your commitment to maintaining our internal security even in the midst of an international crisis has been impressive."

Lucita Azaro

"Yes, the hawks in my house are happy enough with your decision to invade Pales. However..."

Lucita Azaro

"And they are worried that the steps you've taken to democratize Rizia, however well-intentioned, might lead to instability."

Player_Romus

"What about you, Duchess? Do you share that criticism?"

Player_Romus

"I'm doing everything I can. I'd like to see any one of your relatives try ruling the country."

Lucita Azaro

"Be careful what you wish for."

Lucita Azaro

"As a councilor. I'm duty-bound to support my king."

Lucita Azaro

"But as your lover, I hope I'm allowed to hold you to account."

Player_Romus

"Democratizing Rizia will lead to a happier population, which will stabilize the country in the long run."

Lucita Azaro

"And they are worried that the rather Malenyevist posturing you've adopted during your reign will lead to instability on a mass scale."

Player_Romus

"I believe in order, too. But maintaining it requires a light touch, not an iron fist."

Player_Romus

"Improving public welfare will lead to a happier population, which will stabilize the country in the long run."

Lucita Azaro

"They are deeply concerned about the violent protests that have been erupting recently."

Lucita Azaro

"I am trying to do you a service. If my father recovers enough to resume his position on the Royal Council, I fear he will not be as gentle with his feedback."

Narrator

She thought for a moment, then spoke in a measured tone.

Lucita Azaro

"You should know that my father is beginning to make a recovery. If he resumes his position on the Royal Council, I fear he will not be as gentle with his feedback."

Player_Romus

"That old dinosaur, on the Council? He'll be more of a help than a hindrance."

Player_Romus

"That's amazing news! I'm looking forward to working with him again."

Player_Romus

"If he goes against me, he'll be punished. It's as simple as that."

Lucita Azaro

"You cannot punish an entire royal house."

Lucita Azaro

"You haven't even touched your drink yet."

Player_Romus

"Lucita, I think this first date should be our last."

Player_Romus_Italic

I reached for the glass on the table and took a sip.

Lucita Azaro

"It's impudent of me to be troubling you with all this."

Narrator

She shook her head.

Narrator

The water was lightly fizzy, with an aftertaste of lemon.

Narrator

It was a rich, aromatic mix of gin, quince juice and cherry liqueur with a hint of ginger.

Narrator

It was a warming mix of local whiskey, honey, cinnamon and cloves.

Player_Romus

"Liquid courage. Just what I needed."

Narrator

She raised an eyebrow.

Player_Romus

"All this sneaking around isn't for me. I want someone I can be with in the open."

Player_Romus

"Because of the investigation. If anyone finds out I refused to turn you in while I was romantically involved with you, I could be in even worse trouble than I am now."

Player_Romus

"I should have gotten something stronger."

Player_Romus

"Thank you for the company. I'm ready to leave now."

Player_Romus

"I'm going to regret ordering this tomorrow."

Lucita Azaro

"For the gas deal signing?"

Lucita Azaro

"Here's something you won't regret."

Narrator

She leaned across the table and kissed me.

Player_Romus

"Indeed. This will be the ultimate challenge of my reign."

Player_Romus

"To face another day."

Player_Romus

"Courage is always useful. It doesn't matter what it's for."

Player_Romus

"Indeed. It will be a landmark moment in my reign."

Narrator

She frowned for a second, then brightened up.

Lucita Azaro

"I suppose that's sensible. Titus has been waiting long enough."

Player_Romus

"I feel so refreshed."

Lucita Azaro

"If it's refreshing you want..."

Player_Romus

"I would prefer to keep things between us professional. You understand."

Player_Romus

"I have known true love. And it's not what I feel when I'm with you."

Lucita Azaro

"Oh."

Lucita Azaro

"We don't have to worry about being colleagues once I'm off the council."

Lucita Azaro

"Being with me will help your relations with House Azaro in the long run. We just need to wait until I'm off the council."

Lucita Azaro

"We can be together. We just have to wait until I'm off the council."

Player_Romus

"Sorry, Lucita. It's not going to happen."

Narrator

Her eyes flashed in outrage. She responded in an even tone.

Lucita Azaro

"Internally, our national security is not all that it could be. But it's not too late for something to be done about it."

Player_Romus

"And how do they plan to reward me?"

Lucita Azaro

"Shouldn't royal unity be its own reward?"

Lucita Azaro

"Obviously, you can count on the Azaros' full support in the war."

Lucita Azaro

"I've heard rumors that you're trying to make changes to the Rizian government. My family is prepared to back you, as long as you don't go too far."

Player_Romus

"I won't. Incremental change is good for us all."

Player_Romus

"Going too far is the point of my reforms. The old system must die for a new one to be reborn."

Narrator

She smirked.

Lucita Azaro

"Ready to face the next challenge."

Lucita Azaro

"You flatter me, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"Great. Because I've got more investments planned."

Lucita Azaro

"Giving the citizenry a modicum of power can help prevent another uprising. Giving them too much will lead to instability on a mass scale."

Lucita Azaro

"That's how I see it as well. Giving the citizenry too much power at once will result in instability on a mass scale."

Lucita Azaro

"By 'the old system', do you mean you and I? Because we'll be the ones on the chopping block if the citizenry is granted too much power."

Lucita Azaro

"Strong bonds between the Crown and the military have always served this country well."

Player_Romus

"I can, and it chills me to the bone."

Player_Romus

"There's only one way a regime like that can end. With the king's beheading."

Player_Romus

"It's better than a king with absolute power."

Player_Romus

"I'm intrigued. Tell me more."

Lucita Azaro

"The monarch gets to make the popular decisions while the military does the dirty work. Not a bad balance."

Lucita Azaro

"Military officers are willing to die for their country. Why shouldn't they get a chance to rule it?"

Lucita Azaro

"Not if he and the military work together. As a single, well-oiled machine."

Lucita Azaro

"We'll never know whether it would have worked."

Lucita Azaro

"Ask my father about this when you meet him. He's got plenty of opinions about it."

Player_Romus

"That old dinosaur, on the Council? He'll be more of a help than a hindrance."

Player_Romus

"I hope I get the chance."

Player_Romus

"I've heard enough, thanks."

Player_Romus

"First things first. Let's defeat Pales."

Narrator

She shook her head.

Player_Romus

"I've heard enough, thanks."

Lucita Azaro

"He's looking forward to speaking with you. About a great many things."

Lucita Azaro

"Just one."

Narrator

She blinked.

Lucita Azaro

"Don't worry about the drinks, by the way. They're on the house."

Player_Romus

"You read my mind."

Player_Romus

"What's in the VIP suite?"

Narrator

She winked at me and slipped out of the booth.

Lucita Azaro

"It's literally his job."

Player_Romus

"Very well. Lead the way, milady."

Player_Romus

"You thought ahead. How suite of you."

Lucita Azaro

"Our troops will be with you every step of the way. And so will I."

Lucita Azaro

"I didn't know you were on it, Your Majesty."

Lucita Azaro

"I suppose that's sensible. We wouldn't want to get drunk on the eve of declaring war."

Lucita Azaro

"If it's something strong you want..."

Lucita Azaro

"Forget the drink, then."

Lucita Azaro

"Peace between Rizia and Pales, and not a single drop of blood shed. Who would have thought."

Lucita Azaro

"You'll have my help with that. No alcohol necessary."

Lucita Azaro

"You don't need alcohol for that. Remember, Your Majesty, you're not alone."

Player_Romus

"I might as well. Tonight could be our last night together."

Player_Romus

"You know... tonight could be our last night together."

Player_Romus

"I hope you know that buying me a drink doesn't entitle you or any other Azaro to special favors from me."

Player_Romus

"Thank you for bringing me here. I didn't know how much I needed a moment of respite."

Player_Romus

"The next time we come here, that border over there won't exist."

Player_Romus

"I might as well. Who knows what will happen tomorrow?"

Player_Romus

"Thank you for bringing me here. Dare I say my spirits have been lifted?"

Romantic Ending

Player_Romus

"Once a party prince, always a party prince. No use in denying it."

Narrator

She laughed, then quickly assumed a more solemn expression.

Player_Romus

"You, pressuring me? The very idea is ludicrous."

Player_Romus

"I love that I can speak with you so openly. I'd love it even more if we found a more intimate venue to continue this conversation."

Lucita Azaro

"We'll replace it with a monument. To the lives we had to take to defend our sovereignty."

Narrator

We finished our drinks as the city lights twinkled below us.

Lucita Azaro

"My father's aides are astounded by his progress. It won't be long."

Narrator

Leaving my unfinished drink on the table, I followed her to the elevator.

Lucita Azaro

"The drinks are on you tonight, Your Majesty."

Narrator

She slipped out of the booth.

Lucita Azaro

"We should get back to the base. We wouldn't want to keep Titus waiting."

Narrator

She downed the rest of her beverage in one go and hurriedly made her way to the elevator.

Narrator

She groaned and swatted my arm.

Lucita Azaro

"You're an open book, Your Majesty."

Narrator

With a wink, she headed past the bar down a darkened corridor. Leaving my unfinished drink on the table, I followed close behind.

Narrator

She sighed.

Narrator

Lucita and I had just concluded our visit to Terador Air Force Base.

Narrator

Amid the whirlwind of activity, we barely got a chance to speak to each other, let alone discuss the fallout of the border investigation.

"I know you never wanted war. That's why I defended you against the investigation committee's accusations."

Lucita Azaro

"I didn't plan the border attack, Your Majesty."

Lucita Azaro

"Your Majesty, I haven't had the chance to thank you for not giving in to Duke Reinhart's demands for my arrest."

Narrator

She made a scoffing noise.

Player_Romus

"I can't believe Duke Reinhart thought I would turn you in and go back to our gas deal as if nothing had happened."

Lucita Azaro

"But I recognize that turning me in would have been the easiest thing to do."

Lucita Azaro

"I do recognize that turning me in would have been the easiest thing to do."

Player_Romus

"I never thought you were guilty. Mr. Esquibel had his suspicions."

Narrator

She raised her glass. I did the same.

Lucita Azaro

"So you have my gratitude. And that of my family."

Narrator

Still holding my gaze, she took a slow, reflective sip.

Lucita Azaro

"My exoneration aside, I hope you know how much House Azaro appreciates everything you've done for them."

Lucita Azaro

"You're right. We'd have to be idiots to keep seeing each other after this, even in private."

Lucita Azaro

"Don't worry about the drinks tonight, Your Majesty. They're on the house."
